HEADWORD: Marysole
<hw>Ma"ry*sole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mary</ets>,
the proper name + <ets>sole</ets> the fish.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large British fluke, or flounder (<spn>Rhombus megastoma</spn>);
-- called also <altname>carter</altname>, and
<altname>whiff</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

